description: Viking Women: Series 1 History Documentary hosted by Jody Baxmeyer, published by Autentic in 2015 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/4/4e/Viking-Women-Series-1-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ Viking Women: Series 1 The Vikings changed Europe forever, yet half of them have almost completely disappeared from collective memory: the women. Quite unjustly so, as they played an important role in the world of the Vikings and performed extraordinary deeds. Viking women commanded ships and settled colonies. 1) Sigrun's Wrath and the Discovery of Iceland Viking women commanded ships and settled colonies. They took up arms and negotiated with emperors. Their traces can now be discovered all the way from America to Kiev. Without their biographies the period of the Vikings stays incomplete. This is the story of Sigrun, in Norway, in the year 872.
